# Measures of Spread

Measures of spread are also used to analyse quantitative data(variables). Measures of spread are used to provide us with an idea of how spread-out our data are from one another.

This lesson deals with:
1. Evaluating measures of spread:
	* Range
	* Interquartile Range (IQR)
	* Standard Deviation
	* Variance
2. Analyse outliers
3. Evaluate descriptive and inferential statistics.	

## Histograms

Histograms are useful for understanding the different aspects of data and they are a common visual used for quantitative data. Histograms will be used to provide clarity on the four aspects regarding quantitative variables:
	* center
	* spread
	* shape
	* outliers

### How are Histograms constructed
First the data is binned. Each bin represents a range of values in a dataset. The number of values that fall in the range of each bin determines the height of each histogram bar. Changing the bins can result in slightly different visuals, there is no right or wrong way to choosing bins. 	

### Weekdays vs. Weekends

			Weekdays							Weekends
